This paper deals with community detection in multilayer networks, which is a topic that can be approached from different perspectives in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is specifically focused on the analysis of social and information networks, including community detection. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), which includes topics related to software design and development, and can be relevant for the development of optimization methods for community detection. The third most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which includes topics related to the development of algorithms and models for learning from data, and can be relevant for the development of unsupervised approaches for computing modularity. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which includes topics related to the design and analysis of computer networks, and can be relevant for the study of multilayer networks. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which includes topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms and data structures, and can be relevant for the development of efficient methods for community detection.
